    <div class=3D"prose entry-content overflow-clip">
        <p>Like making engineering students squirm? Have them explain convo=
lution and (if you're barbarous) the convolution theorem. They'll mutter so=
mething about sliding windows as they try to escape through one.</p>

<p>Convolution is usually introduced with its formal definition:</p>

<p><img src=3D"https://betterexplained.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-latexrende=
r/pictures/3b38c59c70f4d4c69bbc5d81c2fd0d91.png" width=3D"250" height=3D"43=
" alt=3D"\displaystyle{ (f * g )(t) =3D \int_{-\infty}^\infty f(\tau) g(t -=
 \tau) d\tau }" class=3D"tex"></p>

<p>Yikes. Let's start <em>without</em> calculus: <strong>Convolution is fan=
cy multiplication.</strong></p>

