<h3><span id=3D"Impulse_Response">Impulse Response</span></h3>

<p>What happens if we sent a single patient through the hospital? The convo=
lution would just be that day's plan.</p>

<pre><code>Plan    * Patients =3D Convolution
[3 2 1] * [1]      =3D [3 2 1]
</code></pre>

<p>In other words, convolving with <code>[1]</code> gives us the original p=
lan.</p>

<p>In calculus terms, a spike of <code>[1]</code> (and 0 otherwise) is the =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirac_delta_function">Dirac Delta =
Function</a>. In terms of convolutions, this function acts like the number =
1 and returns the original function:</p>

<p><img src=3D"https://betterexplained.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-latexrende=
r/pictures/b29d7fb1b5d01e09a53c6559aa4b95a8.png" width=3D"132" height=3D"19=
" alt=3D"\displaystyle{f(t) * \delta(t) =3D f(t)}" class=3D"tex"></p>

<p>We can delay the delta function by T, which delays the resulting convolu=
tion function too. Imagine our single patient shows up a week late (<mjx-co=
ntainer class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"SVG" tabindex=3D"0" ct=
xtmenu_counter=3D"40" style=3D"font-size: 95%; position: relative;"><svg xm=
lns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width=3D"7.94ex" height=3D"2.262ex" role=
=3D"img" focusable=3D"false" viewBox=3D"0 -750 3509.4 1000" xmlns:xlink=3D"=
http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical-align:=
