 " data-role=3D"message" dir=3D"auto"><div><p>Sure, this part is tricky. Ou=
r treatment plan is [3 2 1], 3 units on the first day, 2 units on the secon=
d, 1 unit on the third.</p><p>However, if we slide this plan by the patient=
 list<br></p><pre>[3 2 1]<br>    [1 2 3 4 5]<br></pre><p></p><p>We'll see t=
hat the 1st patient seems to get 1 unit on their first day, when the plan s=
aid it was 3. We have to flip the list to [1 2 3] so it's "First in, First =
Out", and the patient will get 3 units on their first day.</p><p></p><pre>[=
1 2 3]<br>    [1 2 3 4 5]<br></pre><p></p><p>If we don't flip the list, we =
get a different calculation (called the correlation), but the convolution r=
equires the flip.</p></div></div><span class=3D"post-media"><ul data-role=
